A prospective cohort study of 13,862 patients showed that among those who underwent
isolated coronary-artery bypass grafting or aortic-valve replacement or repair, the threshold high-sensitivity
cardiac troponin I level (within 1 day after surgery)associated with an adjusted hazard ratio for death within 30
days of more than 1.00 was 5670 ng perliter — 218 times the upper reference limit.
